      "strengths_deep_dive": [
        "OBAT Helpers' operational strength lies in its long-term commitment to infrastructure within displaced communities. Unlike short-term relief agencies, OBAT manages <cite id=\"4\">50 stable educational projects</cite> that provide consistent pathways for youth development. Their financial health is underscored by <cite id=\"10\">5.7 months of operating reserves</cite>, which is considered resilient for an organization of its size. Furthermore, the <cite id=\"13\">100% independent board of directors</cite> ensures high levels of accountability and objective oversight of its <cite id=\"14\">$2.18 million in annual revenue</cite>."
      ],
      "summary": "founded in 2004, OBAT Helpers Inc. is a specialized humanitarian organization dedicated to <cite id=\"1\">lifting displaced and refugee communities out of poverty</cite> in Bangladesh. The organization operates a sophisticated direct-service model that integrates <cite id=\"2\">education, healthcare, and empowerment initiatives</cite> to address the systemic challenges faced by Internally Displaced Persons (IDPs) and Rohingya refugees. With <cite id=\"3\">over 20 years of operational history</cite>, OBAT has established a significant footprint, maintaining <cite id=\"4\">50 educational and training projects</cite> and <cite id=\"5\">3 dedicated health clinics</cite> according to recent audited financials. The organization demonstrates high financial efficiency, characterized by a <cite id=\"6\">program expense ratio of 82.1%</cite> and a remarkably low fundraising cost of <cite id=\"7\">$0.08 per $1 raised</cite>. As a <cite id=\"8\">zakat-eligible entity</cite>, OBAT provides a transparent avenue for Muslim donors to fulfill religious obligations through programs that serve the <cite id=\"9\">fuqara (poor) and masakin (needy)</cite> in one of the world's most densely populated refugee contexts.",
